&lt;p&gt;Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust -Department of Spiritual &amp; Pastoral Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post: 2.8 WTE Band 6 Chaplains – permanent full time and/or part time posts available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ecumenical, multi-faith team of Chaplains which covers both campuses of this Hospital Trust, currently has vacancies for Band 6 Chaplains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit 2.8 WTE permanent Chaplains to expand our large team. We will accept applications from those looking for either full-time or part-time employment (ie 0.6 WTE and above. Hours of posts from 22.5 - 37.5 to be negotiated)). Applicant’s ‘Whole Time Equivalency’ preferences should be indicated clearly on the application form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a Band 6 role and applicants will need to demonstrate healthcare chaplaincy experience, with an aptitude for sensitive pastoral working in this context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will have accreditation/ licensing with authority to practice as a religion or belief (including non-religious beliefs) leader/ representative and/or pastoral worker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves weekend working and daytime and overnight on-call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust is a large teaching hospitals Trust that includes a Children’s Hospital. All Chaplains within our team work generically across all specialisms, however, we welcome applications from those with an aptitude for paediatric chaplaincy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joining one of the larger Chaplaincy departments in the country, it is essential that you are a team player and enjoy working collaboratively. You will be part of a friendly and supportive team, working with colleagues, and in a context, of mixed faith/ belief tradition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please see the Person Specification and Job Description for further clarification and specific details required for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exploratory conversation and informal visits are welcomed. Please contact Revd Andrew Keith, Head of Service at &lt;strong&gt;andrew.keith@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt; 01159 249924 ext 63836 ( (Ext 63836 (x.63799 to leave voicemail).&lt;/p&gt;
